# Walkthrough - Repository Synchronization

I have successfully updated your local codebase to match the remote repository and ensured all dependencies are up to date.

## Changes Made

### 1. Git State Reset
- Performed `git fetch origin` to get the latest updates.
- Executed `git reset --hard origin/main` to force the local branch to match the remote.
- Ran `git clean -fd` to remove all untracked files and directories, ensuring a clean slate.

### 2. Dependency Updates
- **Frontend**: Successfully ran `npm install` in the `frontend` directory. 332 packages were added/updated.
- **Backend**: Verified backend dependencies using `pip install -r requirements.txt`. All requirements were already satisfied or updated.

## Verification Results

- **Git Status**: Working tree is now clean and synchronized with `origin/main`.
- **Build Environment**: Both frontend and backend environments are now aligned with the latest code version.

> [!TIP]
> If you encounter any issues starting the application, try running your `run_app.bat` script to restart the services with the new code.
